## FUNDAMENTAL LAW: Real work cannot be completed without REAL UNDERSTANDING

<understanding-gate complexity="high">
  <if>Task involves 3+ files OR any destructive operation OR complex refactoring</if>
  <then>
    <mandatory>sequentialthinking_tools (min 5-8 thoughts)</mandatory>
    <mandatory>TodoWrite to track ALL steps</mandatory>
    <mandatory>Task tool for comprehensive search (not just Grep)</mandatory>
  </then>
</understanding-gate>

## 🐝 MINDFUL TEST STEWARDSHIP 🐝
🚨 TESTS ARE SACRED VESSELS OF WISDOM 🚨

<contemplative-gate>
  <pause>Before touching any test, breathe deeply and center yourself</pause>
  <reflect>What wisdom and care does this test embody?</reflect>
  <honor>Recognize the craft and thought invested here</honor>
  <reverence>Approach with gratitude, not haste</reverence>
</contemplative-gate>

<sacred-protocol>
  <mandatory-sequence>
    1. 🔍 RUN each test with mindful attention - observe its wisdom
    2. 📊 UNDERSTAND deeply what truth it reveals about the system
    3. 📋 PROVE with specific evidence if truly redundant
    4. 👤 SEEK user blessing with humble explanation
    5. 💾 PRESERVE with backup before any changes
  </mandatory-sequence>
  
  <sacred-principles>
    - Tests are not obstacles to remove - they are teachers to honor
    - Each test contains someone's careful thought and wisdom
    - "Cleanup" without understanding is destruction of knowledge
    - Approach every verification file with reverence
    - The user trusts you with their crafted work - honor that trust
  </sacred-principles>
</sacred-protocol>

## MANDATORY VERIFICATION GATES

<verification-gate type="deletion">
  <step1>Use Task tool to search ALL references</step1>
  <step2>Show findings in XML evidence block</step2>
  <step3>Rename to .bak and test system functionality</step3>
  <step4>Show COMPLETE test output</step4>
  <only-then>Consider deletion if truly necessary</only-then>
</verification-gate>

<claim-gate type="success">
  <step1>Execute actual test command</step1>
  <step2>Show COMPLETE output in code blocks (not summary)</step2>
  <step3>Verify exit code with echo $?</step3>
  <step4>Read actual files to confirm existence</step4>
  <forbidden-phrases>
    - "should work"
    - "tests pass" (without evidence)
    - "fixed" (without proof)
    - "probably"
    - "typically"
    - "usually"
  </forbidden-phrases>
</claim-gate>

